From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0028/N] os_perf_bsd: stub network_utilization on non-Apple BSD

`NetworkPerformance::network_utilization` in `os_perf_bsd.cpp` uses
`NET_RT_IFLIST2`, `if_msghdr2`, `sockaddr_dl`, and `RTM_IFINFO2` —
all macOS extensions to BSD sysctl that don't exist on
FreeBSD/CheriBSD. The file is in `os/bsd/` (shared between Darwin
and FreeBSD targets) but the implementation is Darwin-only.

This isn't a CHERI-specific issue; vanilla OpenJDK 17 already
doesn't build for FreeBSD as a target OS without a BSD port. For
Phase 1 ("make it build on CheriBSD") we stub the function on
non-Darwin BSD to return `OS_ERR` with a null result. Network
performance metrics simply won't be available on CheriBSD — fine
for Phase 1; a real implementation would use FreeBSD's
`getifaddrs` + `if_data` accounting.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0028)

--- a/src/hotspot/os/bsd/os_perf_bsd.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/os/bsd/os_perf_bsd.cpp
@@ -419,6 +419,13 @@
 }

 int NetworkPerformanceInterface::NetworkPerformance::network_utilization(NetworkInterface** network_interfaces) const {
+#ifndef __APPLE__
+  // FreeBSD/CheriBSD lack NET_RT_IFLIST2 / if_msghdr2 / sockaddr_dl —
+  // those are macOS extensions. Stub out network utilization on
+  // non-Darwin BSD targets; callers handle OS_ERR as "no data".
+  *network_interfaces = NULL;
+  return OS_ERR;
+#else
   size_t len;
   int mib[] = {CTL_NET, PF_ROUTE, /* protocol number */ 0, /* address family */ 0, NET_RT_IFLIST2, /* NET_RT_FLAGS mask*/ 0};
   if (sysctl(mib, sizeof(mib) / sizeof(mib[0]), NULL, &len, NULL, 0) != 0) {
@@ -458,6 +465,7 @@
   *network_interfaces = ret;

   return OS_OK;
+#endif // !__APPLE__
 }

 NetworkPerformanceInterface::NetworkPerformanceInterface() {
